	dprr:hasNoteText "Rotondi (304f.) places in 125 the terminus ante quem of the Lex Aebutia which probably limited greatly the application of the legis{511} actiones and increased that of formulae in litigation (Gaius 4.30; cf. Gell. 16.10.8). The date and office of Aebutius remain uncertain." .
